\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Rules:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
These Project Statements should be created together with the matching project.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
As long as the initial project statement is not complete, no new projects
 may be formally created.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Work on new project that cannot be formally created may be placed in temporary
 locations as long as the embargo continues, but it should be minimized
 and finishing the statement should be in high priority.
 This is done in order to avoid having the project directories and files
 without an actual organizing document, and to prevent the state from becoming
 steadily worse until fixing it is unfeasible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Project statements should be updated upon relevant state changes.
 In order to improve accuracy, this should happen as soon as possible (though
 without high priority).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection

\bar under
210606C-2
\bar default
 Progress Statements 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Having created project statements, I now want to create a system that will
 strengthen the integration of my projects and tasks together, to inform
 my decision making at any given point.
 For this reason, the progress statement subsystem instructs the creation
 of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Progress Statements
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, that are similar to the project statements, but refer to multiple projects
 in a specific time scope — specifically, in sequence, 
\family typewriter
Day-Week-Month-Season-Year
\family default
.
 The matching file names are Daily.lyx, Weekly.lyx, Monthly.lyx, Season.lyx
 Yearly.lyx, and they should be updated with each passage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The structure of each Progress is thus:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Outline
\series default
 (What am I going and panning to do during this time scope?)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Overview
\emph default
 — summarize the plan for the times scope in a few sentences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Schedule
\emph default
 — enumerate time-bound (at least in the time scope one-down) events planned
 for this time scope in chronological order, including subject, time and
 place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Statement
\emph default
 — enumerate the minimal work I would like to achieve for the day
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Tasks
\emph default
 — copy a list of tasks from projects, that I would like to engage with
 in the time scope if possible and that the completion of is roughly feasible.
 Detail down to what is relevant to achieve within the time scope one down.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Habits
\emph default
 — enumerate habits to practice in the time scope, and detail time bounds
 if present in the time scope.
 Detail the states of none, partial and full completion of a habit cycle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Embargoes
\emph default
 — enumerate restrictions I would like to set for the time scope.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Status 
\series default
(What is the current state and progress within the outline set for the time
 scope?)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Project Overview
\emph default
 — detail the current rough plan of work for each of the project present
 in the 
\shape slanted
Tasks 
\shape default
section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Habit Overview
\emph default
 — detail the current rough plan of work for each of the project present
 in the 
\shape slanted
Habits 
\shape default
section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Open Issues 
\emph default
— Enumerate current open issues that prevent completion of today's tasks
 and/or habits.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Open Proposals 
\emph default
— Enumerate relevant open proposals (See 
\shape slanted
System210606D
\shape default
)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Results
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Overview
\emph default
 — Summarize the day's passage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Incidents
\emph default
 — Enumerate notable events that have significant effects.t
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Habits
\emph default
 — Detail attempts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Failures
\emph default
 — Enumerate failed attempts to complete habits or tasks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Task
\emph default
 
\emph on
Closure
\emph default
 — enumerate tasks closed in the time scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Issue Closure
\emph default
 — enumerate tasks closed in the time scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
New Issues
\emph default
 — Enumerate issues opened today
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Conclusions
\series default
 (What did I learn in this time scope)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Proposal Closure
\emph default
 — enumerate proposals closed in the time scope, and their resolution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
New Proposals
\emph default
 — Enumerate proposals opened in the time scope.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Lessons — 
\emph default
General insights from the time scope.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Before each object, a tag [PROJECT] should note the project it belongs to,
 or otherwise the aspect it's under, if there is no specific project.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the 
\emph on
Daily
\emph default
 statement, append to the results section
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Rest
\emph default
 — enumerate rests in the day by type and content
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Mood
\emph default
 — Name mood level 0-1 for Start, Max, Min, End, Average
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the 
\shape slanted
Season
\shape default
 statement, the Overview section should also declare the season's theme,
 and enumerate plans for each aspect.
\end_layout

